=== dressed_second_talk ===
What do you intend to leave behind? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left #character:npc14
Pardon? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
After you have died, what do you leave behind from the life you lived? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Uhhh.. wow… #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I’ll probably leave behind a bunch of stuff that my friends and family can take. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
And I’m hoping to leave behind a lot of people who love me, as sad as that would be for them. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
I haven’t really ever thought about having kids or anything so I don’t know about that… #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Those are meaningless things, do you not aim to be remembered through the ages? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
To do great deeds that shape the world? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Uhhh… I’m sorry, but why do I have to? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
What? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Why do I have to do that? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
You don’t <i>have</i> to, but why do you lack ambition? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I don’t lack ambition, just cause I don’t want to be the one person who changes the whole world doesn’t mean I don’t have ambitions. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I want to be kind to the people close to me, make a life for myself in whatever that means. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Like yeah I want to help the people around me and do good and stuff. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
But working towards some abstract idea of greatness or being known forever that doesn’t really seem that important or desirable to me. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Honestly it’s kind of selfish if you think about. Only doing things, even good things, to further your own name or legacy or whatever. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
You don’t care about anyone but yourself. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Selfish?! #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
But hundreds even thousands of lives could be changed for the better by the actions of one. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Yeah, and that’s good, but you aren’t doing it for them are you? You aren’t doing it truly help a person out or else you wouldn’t feel the need to attach your name to it. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
You wouldn’t obsess over if your actions ensure your place in history for everyone forever. If you really cared. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
You’d just, do it. You’d just help. And sometimes maybe not even expect anything back. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
So your saying philanthropy is purely for vanity? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Yeah cause it is. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
And if you are in position to have that much money that giving it away to charities is like, a fun hobby for you. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I would say it’s not just vanity but you’re probably just attempting to pay away some of the bad you’ve done to get that money. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
No rich person has ever gotten their money without ruining more than a couple lives. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I cannot believe that! #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Well believe it or not, it’s true. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Once you see almost a whole town lose their jobs overnight because one person decided that the labour of hundreds of people wasn’t fast enough despite them doing good work so they close up the factory and move it to another city. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
You make money by ruining lives, it’s just how it is. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I would never do something like that. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Sure, you wouldn’t, but there are people around you definitely would. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
And if you pay the salary for the man who fires my dad? Well shit, you got some hand in that, sorry to say. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
… #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I don’t know what to say… #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
I don’t know, you can say that sucks? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Yes, you’re right, that does indeed, “suck”. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Mhmm. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Tell me about it. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
… #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
