=== dressed_third_talk ===
So if I’m not to ensure my legacy through philanthropy or business then how shall I do it? You seem to have some insights into this world that I don’t. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left #character:npc14
Uhhh I have no idea. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_thinking #layout:right
You can invent something important and that would help the whole world.  #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_thinking #layout:right
But… there’s a good chance people will just use that to exploit others or make money so that’s not an inherent good anymore. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
You could start a charity and not have your name associated with it and just give people your money. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_thinking #layout:right
But like, also don’t use the charity to make more money for yourself, I know there are plenty of rich people who raise money for a “charity” but it’s just more money for themselves. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Ugghhh. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I don’t know, man. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Be nice to people. Stop trying to be so important. Volunteer your time. Give people who need money some money. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
It’s really not that hard but it also is. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Like I’ve been worrying that I’ve not been doing enough in my life by putting my whole life on pause and dropping out of school and moving back home to help my family. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I work and contribute to my family and I try to help the people in my town that are also having a hard time. And every damn day I feel so guilty that I’m not helping out enough, that I’m not good enough. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Even though I’m running myself ragged trying to do things for others while I’m just… not… happy. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
And you’re here asking for the easiest solution to be a good person. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Like I’m sorry I don’t know. I don’t know because I don’t even feel like it some days and I don’t have tons of money like it seems you do, which would literally solve all my problems. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I see. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I apologize for my inquiry, I see now it was tactless. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Yeah, well, whatever. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
