=== dressed_fourth_talk ===
So, you have a family? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left #character:npc14
Yeah, I got a little brother and sister and my parents. And also lots of cousins and aunts and uncles and stuff that I see sometimes. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
I have a family as well, a wife and two children. A daughter and a son. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
That’s nice. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
I also understand you conflicts around… familial obligation. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Oh? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Yes. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I work to ensure that my children are in the best schools. My son soon will be graduating top of his class in pre-medicine from the University of Eden. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
And my daughter is training to be a dancer with the National Dance Company and requires a number of trainers and tutors. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I know that my children will be the best in their respective fields and so I must fund all the opportunities that ensure they achieve their fullest potential. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Wow.. That’s uh.. Cool. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
It is quite “cool” I suppose. They are wonderful children and will go on to do great things. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Are they happy? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Excuse me? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Are they happy? Do they like what they are doing? Being the best at whatever it is they are doing. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
They are both very driven and ambition and have chased down these opportunities equal to or exceeding the help they have received. They have quite clear minds about their futures. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Yeah but like, are they happy? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Do they like what they do? Are they happy to be a dancer or a doctor or whatever? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Well I would assume through pursuing the things they are passionate they would be happy? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
So you don’t know? If your kids are happy? Or if they are just working hard to do something important or be the best at something? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I… #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
It’s really easy to be miserable while chasing down the thing that you think you should be, trust me, I know. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
How do you know? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Because at many points in my life I’ve just worked so hard to be the thing I thought I wanted to be. Or, truly, I was trying to be the thing that my parents wanted me to be. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
But that wasn’t who I was or what I wanted for myself, and it made me miserable. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
It still does.. Kind of… I’m still kind of doing it I guess. Living for them. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
And you aren’t happy? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
God no. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Like okay, I have some nice moments with my family. I love my siblings. My parents are okay, but they don’t make it easy for me. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I’m not really like them and they have a hard time knowing how to talk to me, or understand me, or even letting me exist… #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
I see. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I fear I do not know if my children are happy or not. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
That is a catatrophic oversight on my behalf. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Well, at least you can admit it! #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
I’m sure things aren’t as hard for them cause they don’t have to work a job to feed you. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
<i>Laughs.</i> #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Sorry, that was inappropriate. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
It is alright. It offers me a frame of reference that I feel is much needed. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Oh, well… you’re welcome? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Yes, thank you for your conversation. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I see I have been misguided on some important things for far too long. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
Hey, never too late to admit you were wrong about stuff. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
… Indeed. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_sad #layout:left
How can I repay you for services? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Aw, it’s nothing. Helping out people without getting anything back, that’s what it’s all about right? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
As you said, and so I wish to help, without expectations. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Well if you could find a way to get everyone in my town their jobs back, that would peachy. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_thinking #layout:right
I could see to that. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Wow, really? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Yes, I’m certain I could have something arranged. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Uh, wow, okay. Thanks so much. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
No thanks needed, help without reciprocation, yes? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_happy #layout:left
Yeah. Well, still thanks. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
