=== dressed_fifth_talk ===
Was this some sort of textile mill that was in your town? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left #character:npc14
Uh, yeah, a linen processing plant. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_thinking #layout:right
Excellent. I will see to it that services resume. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Seriously? You aren’t messing with me? #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
I am looking to make an attempt at your advice on how to help others. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
And I can surely afford to purchase a textile mill. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_happy #layout:left
Wow okay… #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Though if you really want to help. You should let the workers own it and run it. They know the work better than anyone else and it’s been in our town for decades.  #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
All our problems stemmed from people owning it who never worked a day there in their lives. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_sad #layout:right
Purchase the mill and then resell it to its employees? #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
Yeah. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Hmm.. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_neutral #layout:left
I will consider it. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_happy #layout:left
Okay cool. #speaker: Peyton #portrait:mc_happy #layout:right
Yes, cool. #speaker:Well Dressed Man #portrait:npc14_happy #layout:left
